OL,6,FRowan Perry-Lee is one of many now
OL,7,Ffacing an uncertain future. She's been
OL,8,Fa tenant of Homes for Reading for the
OL,9,Flast six years.JRowan, whose husband
OL,10,Fis a key worker himself, says the
OL,11,Fproposal just doesn't make sense.J"A
OL,12,Flot of the tenants who are in these
OL,13,Fhomes are keyworkers. My husband is a
OL,14,Fteacher who is actually employed by
OL,15,FReading Borough Council. We got the
OL,16,Fletter through on the 19th of
OL,17,FFebruary, it was a bombshell and it's
OL,18,Fjust been a nightmare since then."
